<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3690] Work around docker image build failures on Travis-CI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3690</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As each of 24 jobs build downloads or builds a docker image, one or two of them has been constantly failing.&lt;br/&gt;
It should be alleviated by introducing retry and also disabling the 10 min auto failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, according to the doc, travis-ci env has 2 cores.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/ci-environment/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/ci-environment/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
So I&apos;m changing make -j4 -&amp;gt; -j3 for now to see if it reduces some test flakiness for free.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
